&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must-have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years in &lt;strong&gt;performance marketing, creative strategy, or growth marketing&lt;/strong&gt; roles (e.g. Creative Strategist, UA Manager, Growth Creative Lead, Marketing Manager)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A portfolio showing &lt;strong&gt;data-driven creative concepts&lt;/strong&gt; that delivered measurable results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of &lt;strong&gt;paid social creative performance&lt;/strong&gt; and testing methodologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills — able to translate insights into compelling creative directions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in English and a natural ability to craft ideas for a global (especially US) audience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with creative production workflows, without needing to be hands-on in editing tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with project management tools (Jira, Confluence, Google Workspace)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curiosity for new formats, cultural trends, and emerging AI creative tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An obsession with results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
